snippet: After more than 35 years in the House, Representative Norm Dicks, a Democrat representing Washington state's 6th District, said he won't seek re-election because he and his wife want a change of pace.
abstract: After more than 35 years in the House, Representative Norm Dicks, a Democrat representing Washington state's 6th District, said he won't seek re-election because he and his wife want a change of pace.

headline.main: Washington State Lawmaker Will Not Seek Re-election
headline.print_headline: Filing Out: Washington Democrat to Retire
